<br>
Ender's Game doesn't hold my interest as much anymore as an individual book, I greatly prefer Ender's Shadow in terms of telling the same story.  If you keep reading the series I suggest you read Shadow of the Hegemon and Shadow Puppets before you go back on the other branch of the series (Speaker for the Dead, Xenocide, and Children of the Mind).  The Shadow Series leaves Ender behind and focuses more on his legacy, and while the Ender Series is good, it becomes more philosophical whereas the Shadow Series terms more political in nature.<br>
<br>
