WoT - the story is great, the (male) characters are good, but he isn't a very good writer.<br>
<br>
Let me tell you what brought me out of the darkness: GEORGE R R MARTIN.  I can't sing this man's praises enough - read A Song of Ice and Fire and you'll weep because, you know, that if Martin had written The Wheel of Time it'd be a fucking religion by now.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, just read A Song of Ice and Fire - the first book is A Game of Thrones.  I promise you, you will not be dissapointed whatsoever. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub114.ezboard.com/blegacyofsteel43089.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tikker>Tikker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gnome Down!</span><br>  Posts: 2067<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/14/03 4:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3790.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~dbichara/tikker.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tikker..</span><hr size=1> our personal tastes vary then =P<br>
