<br>
Another series that I just got hooked on is Malazan Book of the Fallen series by Steven Erikson.  First book is Gardens of the Moon.  Its apparently going to be a 10 book &quot;series&quot; where each book is a standalone taking place in the same world.  <br>
<br>
I'm only in the middle of the first book (theres 4 available atm), but the plot is extremely complex and you're not too sure who is the good guy in it.  Lots of backstabbing and treachery.  Has a form of magic, undead, and some other fantasy traits.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately it has to be imported from the UK in most cases since no US publisher has picked it up yet.  Check out www.abebooks.com or www.amazon.co.uk for em if yer intersted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub114.ezboard.com/blegacyofsteel43089.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hakarulez>Hakarulez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/17/03 4:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3790.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> should read the earths children series.  great books and very well layed out by the author who does large quantities of research for each novel.   <br>
